OL,3,CMan, 41, lost leg after excavator
OL,4,Creverses into him at work
OL,6,FHowever, these precautions were not
OL,7,Fbeing used in practice. There was also
OL,8,Fno monitoring of the alleged systems
OL,9,Fin place, had there been, this would
OL,10,Fhave highlighted that the control
OL,11,Fmeasures were not being used.
OL,13,FThe company pleaded guilty to
OL,14,Fbreaching regulation 2(1) of the
OL,15,FHealth and Safety at Work etc Act
OL,16,F1974. It was fined #106,700 and
OL,17,Fordered to pay #5,744 costs at a
OL,18,Fhearing at Manchester Magistrates'
OL,19,FCourt on 7 August 2024.
